The set up for this game will be Bloodhound and Werewolf vs Harlot, Protector, Stalker, Militia, 2 Vanilla and a Sleepwalker.
Bloodhound is a Wolf that can check players roles at night.
Harlot will see who visits their target
Protector will stop the kill if the Wolves try and kill their target, but they can't protect the same person twice in a row
Stalker will see who their target visits
Militia can, once per game, choose to kill someone at night.
Vanilla have no powers, so you need to figure out what's going on.
And Sleepwalker is told they're Vanilla, but actually will visit someone at night.
I can set it to go now if that makes things better?
Say "Oi" if you're ready to play.
There are: 1 Bloodhound, 1 Werewolf, 1 Harlot, 1 Protector, 1 Militia, 1 Stalker, 2 Villagers and 1 Sleepwalker.
